data.description: TENNESSEE MOUNTAIN HOMESTEAD WITH A CREEK FOR SALE NEAR GATLINBURG TN! Now is your chance to experience country living at it's best!! This charming 1949 home has tons of character and potential sealed inside ready for you to make your own! Want to feel like you're a real homesteader from the 1950's? Seller is including a 1950 Ford Jubilee Tractor with the sale that you can use to manage your mini farm! Sitting on over 4 acres and bordering COSBY CREEK this homestead is ready for your new adventures! Incredible features include: barn, goat pen, mostly level ground, perfect mix of fields and woodlands, various wild fruit vines and native walnut trees, shared well and shared septic with deeded rights to use, front porch perfect for rocking chairs and sweet tea, original hardwood flooring in good condition, original shiplap walls, convenient floorplan, and so much more! Learn more about East Tennessee genealogy by visiting the small cemetery joining the backside of the property with the oldest grave dating to 1892! ONLY 25 MINS TO GATLINBURG and GREAT SMOKY MOUNTAIN NATIONAL PARK, 47 MINUTES TO NEW BUC-CEES IN KODAK TN, and SHORT DRIVE TO KNOXVILLE TN!  **Home is being offer As-Is for $180,000 or can be finished to seller's specs for $250,000**. Call today to schedule your tour!*Information provided as a courtesy, believed to be correct, and obtained from tax records and/or current owner of the property. Buyer to verify all important information and exercise due diligence before entering an agreement to purchase real estate.*
